<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Well, this is <a href=3D"https://link.mail.blo=
ombergbusiness.com/click/32060626.265406/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9hcnRpY2=
xlcy93ZWFsdGhpZXN0LW9pbG1hbi1ob3VzdG9uLWhpbGRlYnJhbmQtY2xpbWF0ZS1hY3Rpdmlzb=
S0zMmJiOGFlYz9tb2Q9aXRwX3dzaiZydT15YWhvbw/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBb5435b23=
" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D=
"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px=
; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-colo=
r: #ccc;"> not an=C2=A0<em>unrelated=C2=A0</em>mechanism</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Climate activists and Wall Street are making i=
t tougher for Big Oil to stay in the oil business. They=E2=80=99ve also hel=
ped make Jeffery Hildebrand a multibillionaire.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Hildebrand, who is little known outside his ho=
metown of Houston, has become one of America=E2=80=99s largest independent =
drillers by buying assets on the cheap, cutting costs and then squeezing ou=
t both oil and profit from wells that others left for dead. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">It=E2=80=99s a business model that is growing =
from a niche into a juggernaut as the industry=E2=80=99s giants, facing mou=
nting calls to cut their carbon emissions, dial back on drilling and shed a=
ssets. Hilcorp is privately held so it doesn=E2=80=99t face ESG demands=E2=
=80=94short for environmental, social and governance issues=E2=80=94from in=
vestors. That means the pressure on big oil companies isn=E2=80=99t necessa=
rily leading to less pumping, but rather pumping by less-accountable player=
s.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Hilcorp has become a natural clearinghouse for=
 big oil companies looking to unload aging wells that may leak copious amou=
nts of methane, a powerful atmosphere-warming gas.=C2=A0...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Between 2017 and 2021, companies with methane-=
reduction goals sold $115.6 billion worth of assets to firms that don=E2=80=
=99t have explicit targets for reduction, the Environmental Defense Fund sa=
id in a report last year.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Over that same period, Hilcorp bought more tha=
n $9 billion worth of assets from companies including an Exxon Mobil affili=
ate, ConocoPhillips and BP, according to a tally by energy analytics firm E=
nverus.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">My general model of ESG and carbon emissions g=
oes something like this:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">ESG investors raise the cost of capit=
al of carbon-emitting projects, by refusing to invest in companies with exc=
essive emissions, or by investing in those companies but pressuring their e=
xecutives to get rid of the most carbon-emitting assets.</li>=09<li style=
=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">One effect of this is to cause public companies to=
 get rid of their most carbon-emitting assets, to lower their cost of capit=
al (and avoid pressure from shareholders).</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-botto=
m: 5px;">Another effect=C2=A0is to cause the=C2=A0<em>buyers=C2=A0</em>of t=
hese assets to have <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/clic=
k/32060626.265406/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzL=
zIwMjMtMDMtMjIvc2lsaWNvbi12YWxsZXktYmFuay1yYW4tb3V0LW9mLW1vbmV5P2NtcGlkPUJC=
RDA3MTIyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGV=
yJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMDcxMiZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a31=
9a23cB6f72f136" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_b=
lank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bot=
tom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; b=
ackground-color: #ccc;">  a higher cost of capital and thus=C2=A0</a><em><a=
 href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32060626.265406/aHR0=
cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDMtMjIvc2lsaWN=
vbi12YWxsZXktYmFuay1yYW4tb3V0LW9mLW1vbmV5P2NtcGlkPUJCRDA3MTIyM19NT05FWVNUVU=
ZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMDcxM=
iZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cC6f72f136" itempr=
op=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: =
#000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border=
-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;=
">a shorter time horizon</a>:=C2=A0</em>If your cost of capital is high, th=
en a dollar today is worth more than a dollar in 10 years, so you will pump=
 all the oil now.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Another effect i=
s to cause the buyers of those assets to systematically=C2=A0<em>care less =
about emissions=C2=A0</em>than the sellers: If you care a lot about emissio=
ns (because you have ESG-focused shareholders and are trying to meet ESG go=
als), you will do what you can to limit emissions from whatever assets you =
own, but if you are explicitly in the business of buying everyone else=E2=
=80=99s most carbon-emitting assets then you are not going to get any ESG c=
redit and so might as well go nuts on the emissions.</li>=09<li style=3D"ma=
rgin-bottom: 5px;">Another effect is to cause the buyers of those assets=C2=
=A0to get rich: =E2=80=9CThe cost of capital of aging oil wells is high=E2=
=80=9D <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32060626.26=
5406/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDctMD=
gvc29tZW9uZS1pcy1nb2luZy10by1kcmlsbC10aGUtb2lsP2NtcGlkPUJCRDA3MTIyM19NT05FW=
VNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIz=
MDcxMiZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB40ed88e7" i=
temprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"co=
lor: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; b=
order-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: =
#ccc;">  is another way of saying</a> =E2=80=9Cthe expected return=C2=A0on =
equity of owning aging oil wells is high.=E2=80=9D</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This story is all of those things.</p>
