<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The way I thought of the boom in private tech =
companies in the late 2010s was that there was a lot of global capital avai=
lable to be invested in tech companies, and relatively few tech ideas and e=
ntrepreneurs that could plausibly achieve global scale. Entrepreneurs were =
in demand, capital was cheap and plentiful, and so you got not only enormou=
s valuations but also very founder-friendly terms for big private tech inve=
stments.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In 2023 it seems somehow appropriate that ther=
e is a glut of private equity firms and a shortage of plumbers. Bloomberg=
=E2=80=99s=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32=
060626.265406/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtM=
DctMTIvd2h5LXByaXZhdGUtZXF1aXR5LWlzLWNoYXNpbmctcGx1bWJlcnMtYW5kLWx1bWJlci15=
YXJkcz9jbXBpZD1CQkQwNzEyMjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3V=
yY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMzA3MTImdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/60=
7f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBf95ea34e" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemsc=
ope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !impo=
rtant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-botto=
m-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">Michael Sasso reports</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Local plumbers and lumber-yard owners across t=
he US are feeling a bit like tech entrepreneurs of late =E2=80=94 juggling =
multiple offers from private equity-backed firms that increasingly are targ=
eting mom-and-pop businesses.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Wall Street has been buying into fragmented Ma=
in Street industries for years, with dental and veterinary practices among =
the favorite targets. It=E2=80=99s known as the roll-up strategy =E2=80=93 =
and it=E2=80=99s catching a tailwind right now, and expanding rapidly in ho=
usehold services and building materials. ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In the Atlanta area, Jay Cunningham says he ge=
ts several pitches a week from PE-backed firms wanting to buy his Superior =
Plumbing =E2=80=94 one of the few sizeable local firms that hasn=E2=80=99t =
already been snapped up by investors =E2=80=94 or from investment bankers w=
anting to bring Superior to market. He=E2=80=99s not interested.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CI probably think they=E2=80=99re a nu=
isance as a whole,=E2=80=9D Cunningham says. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">John Loud<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#=
footnote-6" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: no=
ne !important; background-color: transparent !important; display: inline-bl=
ock;">
<span>[6]</span>
</a>=C2=A0gets as many as 30 solicitations a month for his Kennesaw, Georgi=
a-based alarm installation firm, Loud Security Systems, which has about 60 =
employees and more than $7 million in annual revenue.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CIt=E2=80=99s a non-stop barrage,=E2=
=80=9D Loud says, and it=E2=80=99s been going on for years. He used to joke=
 with employees: =E2=80=9CIf you want job security, save me from these call=
s and these emails.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There=E2=80=99s a business idea there. You sta=
rt a=C2=A0middle-market investment bank=C2=A0and you go out to small busine=
sses saying =E2=80=9Cfor a $1,000 annual retainer, you can send=C2=A0every =
investment firm who contacts you a form email saying that I am your investm=
ent banker and they should work through me, and then I will put their pitch=
es in the garbage so you don=E2=80=99t have to.=E2=80=9D<a class=3D"footnot=
e-index" href=3D"#footnote-7" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: non=
e !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; borde=
r-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transparent !important; =
display: inline-block;">
<span>[7]</span>
</a> PE-Be-Gone. Surely there are a few thousand clients who=E2=80=99d want=
 that; here are two, anyway.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Sasso notes some economic factors driving priv=
ate equity to spend more on roll-ups=C2=A0(plumbing is relatively recession=
-proof, small private companies are cheaper, public ones are too averse to =
selling at below-peak valuations). But the deep supply-and-demand story the=
re might be something like =E2=80=9CUS society pushes young people into col=
lege rather than the trades, and then colleges push ambitious students=C2=
=A0into private equity, and the result is that we have way too many private=
 equity investors and way too few plumbers.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0</p>
