<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Inside Tesla, it was known as =E2=80=9CProject=
 42,=E2=80=9D and the plans called for a dramatic glass-walled building to =
rise near the automaker=E2=80=99s headquarters outside this capital city.=
=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Internally, the secret project was described a=
s a house for Chief Executive=C2=A0Elon Musk.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One concept showed a structure in the shape of=
 a twisted hexagon on waterfront land with Tesla=E2=80=99s factory in the b=
ackground, according to a document reviewed by The Wall Street Journal.=C2=
=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Other renderings depicted an expansive glass b=
ox, reminiscent of Apple=E2=80=99s store on Fifth Avenue in Manhattan, with=
 a residential area that appeared to include bedrooms, bathrooms and a kitc=
hen, said people familiar with the matter. ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Along the way, the project drew scrutiny from =
Tesla lawyers and board members, according to people with knowledge of the =
situation. An order for millions of dollars in specialized glass=E2=80=94th=
e type of large-format panels used on building facades=E2=80=94sparked conc=
ern among some employees about what the materials would be used for, some o=
f the people said.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">After that order, Tesla board members investig=
ated whether company resources had been misused and if Musk, himself, had a=
 role, some people with knowledge of the situation said.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Look honestly I think spending millions of dol=
lars to build a giant glass house for Elon Musk right near Tesla headquarte=
rs is a <em>good</em> use of corporate funds? Keep an eye on him. Really if=
 the board had thought of this I would be praising it as an innovative corp=
orate governance idea.=C2=A0You can=E2=80=99t necessarily make Elon Musk wa=
rn you when he=E2=80=99s going to <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbus=
